From: darkloom integration
Subject: [PATCH] whatsapp: route aiohttp sessions through gateway proxy resolver

WhatsApp adapter creates aiohttp.ClientSession instances without
consulting the gateway's centralized proxy resolver. This means
WhatsApp traffic bypasses Tor even when ALL_PROXY is set.

This patch adds resolve_proxy_url() + proxy_kwargs_for_aiohttp()
to all aiohttp session creation sites, using the WHATSAPP_PROXY
env var (with fallback to ALL_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY/HTTP_PROXY).

Fixes: whatsapp adapter bypassing gateway-level Tor proxy
Related: darkloom gateway integration
---
 plugins/platforms/whatsapp/adapter.py | 27 ++++++++++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/plugins/platforms/whatsapp/adapter.py b/plugins/platforms/whatsapp/adapter.py
index WHATSAPP_INDEX..WHATSAPP_INDEX 100644
--- a/plugins/platforms/whatsapp/adapter.py
+++ b/plugins/platforms/whatsapp/adapter.py
@@ -31,6 +31,11 @@ from hermes_constants import (
     find_node_executable,
     get_hermes_dir,
     with_hermes_node_path,
+)
+from gateway.platforms.base import (  # ADD THESE IMPORTS
+    resolve_proxy_url,
+    proxy_kwargs_for_aiohttp,
 )
 
